*strlen*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

strlen â€” Get string length

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  strlen(string $string): int~

Returns the length of the given {string}.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{string}

  The string being measured for length.

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The length of the {string} in bytes.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 A strlen() example

<?php >
  $str = 'abcdef';
  echo strlen($str); // 6

  $str = ' ab cd ';
  echo strlen($str); // 7
<?>

===============================================================================
[ Notes ]

  Note:

  strlen() returns the number of bytes rather than the number of characters in
  a string.

===============================================================================
